results.overview:
PS 14 The Fairview School is located in the Heart of Corona. Founded in 1914, we have deep connections to Queens, rich with history and tradition. Do you know why our school is named âThe Fairview Schoolâ? Itâs because we had a view of the Worldâs Fairs in 1939 and 1964. The â39 theme was âThe World of Tomorrowâ, and the â64 theme was "Peace through Understanding" dedicated to "Man's Achievement on a Shrinking Globe in an Expanding Universe". We embrace those themes, and we recently rebranded ourselves as a "Sustainable STEAM School" with STEM themed classes, a heavy emphasis on the arts, and a hydroponics lab with Family Gardening Hour. We are a Billion Oyster School, and every child takes both engineering and computer science every single year. 

At PS 14 we believe that all children have talents and strengths. We strive to engage all students in enriching and inspiring ways. All students take at least one semester of the following courses EVERY year from kindergarten through fifth grade: dance, theater, music/piano, engineering, computer science 4 all, and "SEL through Visual Arts". We believe in kindness and courage, and we believe that adults and children alike are ultimately responsible for our own learning, growth, and improvement. As a Leader in Me school, we practice 8 Habits of Highly Effective People with a goal of âowning our own learning.â Students have voice and choice in their learning, and we partner with parents â the people who know their children best â to best support all students. A variety of Saturday programs run all school-year long for adults, teens, and PS 14 students including a robust cadets program. 

Our arts department is our pride and joy. Our PS 14 Star Choir broadcast locally and nationally on the 2022 Rockefeller Tree Lighting Special. Our band, choir, and theater kids are invited all over the city to perform, including recently: Carnegie Hall, The Queens Borough Arts Fair, The Department of Education Tweed Building, Queens Museum, Queens Borough Hall, the 110 Precinct Events, and the annual Corona Tree Lighting. Our musical theater department puts up shows annually, and recently performed High School Musical Jr, Aladdin Jr., Frozen Jr., and our 2025 show is Moana Jr. Come and watch us perform at 5 pm on June 12 and June 13, 2025!

We are a UFT Community School, offering wrap around services for members of our community, including ESL classes for adults, an after-school Beacon program (until 6 pm, grades 1-5 only), and after school clubs for our upper grade students. K -2 students engage in gradewide clubs during the school day. 

We value our Sustainable STEAM theme. Our Annual STEM Expo is a highlight every March.  In addition to our Hydroponics Lab, we have one of the only Black Box Theaters in any NYC elementary school. Our dance studio with wood floors, ballet barres, and mirrors is currently being built. We have a Computer Science Lab (including robots to code), an Engineering Lab with 3D printers, a Visual Arts Room, and a Music and the Brain Keyboard Lab. Our main theater is newly renovated with a new stage, and our library is undergoing an upgrade as well to include comfortable seating and a place for students to read or study during lunchtime. Oh, and we have two small soccer pitches and a 1/20 mile track in our backyard. 

Next up: we are building a Play Garden with room for three outdoor classrooms and on the corner of 108th and Martense. The plan is to open this space in the fall of 2026.

And there is so much more that we offer our students and our families. To learn more, please visit us at www.PS14Fairview.org and follow us on Instagram at PS14Fairview. 

We can't wait to meet you!

results.overview: The Marino Jeantet school is a Community School in the heart of Corona. We pride ourselves on being a hub of the community at large offering robust services to both students and families.  We are a United Community School offering support to families in the form of food pantries, clothing closets, dental services and mental health services. Although we are the largest elementary school in NY, we create a family like culture though our monthly family events, parent workshops, and close Parent Association collaboration. We have afterschool programs Monday-Friday ranging from academic to extracurricular to ensure we are enriching the whole child. Our goal is to expose students to various, impactful experiences inside and outside of school to prepare students for their future.  Through our academic programs, school initiatives and strong community partnerships we aim to send students to middle school ready to begin college or career planning for a future of their choice. This school has a Bilingual Special Education (BSE) program: Open to students recommended for Bilingual Special Education (BSE) on their Individualized Education Plan (IEP). If your child is recommended for BSE on their IEP and you have questions, visit www.schools.nyc.gov/specializedprograms or contact BSEprograms@schools.nyc.gov.
